Join basins to occurrence dataset

rfs_join_basins.Rd

This function joins basins to an occurrence dataset based on shapefiles. The return is used by rFishStatus::rfs_detect_invasive().

Usage

rfs_join_basins(occ_df, shapefile = "br_pr_basins")

Arguments

occ_df

A data frame of occurrences obtained from rFishStatus::rfs_update_occ_data().

shapefile

A character string specifying the shapefiles contained in the package. The default is "br_pr_basins". The user can also provide a shapefile directly in sf format. Obs.: for now, only the shapefile "br_pr_basins" is available directly from the package. New opstions will be added in the future.

Value

A data frame of the joined occurrences and basins.

Examples

occ_df <- rFishStatus:::data_occ_update_result
rfs_join_basins(occ_df, "br_pr_basins")
